gp/js-h/1.html?verse=8#p8" href="/scriptures/pgp/js-h/1.8?lang=spa#p8">José Smith—Historia 1:8</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note7-"><span class="label">7. </span><p data-aid="138770924" id="note7_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/pgp/js-h/1.html?verse=10#p10" href="/scriptures/pgp/js-h/1.10?lang=spa#p10">José Smith—Historia 1:10</a>; negrilla agregada.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note8-"><span class="label">8. </span><p data-aid="138770926" id="note8_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/nt/acts/10.html?verse=38#p38" href="/scriptures/nt/acts/10.38?lang=spa#p38">Hechos 10:38</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note9-"><span class="label">9. </span><p data-aid="138770927" id="note9_p1">Bonnie D. Parkin, “Personal Ministry: Sacred and Precious” (Devocional en la Universidad Brigham Young, 13 de febrero de 2007), pág. 1, speeches.byu.edu.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note10-"><span class="label">10. </span><p data-aid="138770931" id="note10_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/bofm/moro/7.html?verse=13#p13" href="/scriptures/bofm/moro/7.13?lang=spa#p13">Moroni 7:13</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note11-"><span class="label">11. </span><p data-aid="138770932" id="note11_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/nt/1-cor/13.html?verse=8#p8" href="/scriptures/nt/1-cor/13.8?lang=spa#p8">1 Corintios 13:8</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note12-"><span class="label">12. </span><p data-aid="138770935" id="note12_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/bofm/2-ne/32.html?verse=5#p5" href="/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/32.5?lang=spa#p5">2 Nefi 32:5</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note13-"><span class="label">13. </span><p data-aid="138770937" id="note13_p1">“Todo lo puedo en Cristo que me fortalece” (<a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/nt/philip/4.html?verse=13#p13" href="/scriptures/nt/philip/4.13?lang=spa#p13">Filipenses 4:13</a>).</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note14-"><span class="label">14. </span><p data-aid="138770939" id="note14_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/nt/heb/4.html?verse=16#p16" href="/scriptures/nt/heb/4.16?lang=spa#p16">Hebreos 4:16</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note15-"><span class="label">15. </span><p data-aid="138770941" id="note15_p1">“Y si los hombres vienen a mí, les mostraré su debilidad… entonces haré que las cosas débiles sean fuertes para ellos” (Éter 12:27). Doy a los hombres debilidad para que sean humildes; y basta mi <em>gracia</em> a todos los hombres que se humillan ante mí; porque si se humillan ante mí, y tienen fe en mí, entonces haré que las cosas débiles sean fuertes para ellos” (<a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/bofm/ether/12.html?verse=27#p27" href="/scriptures/bofm/ether/12.27?lang=spa#p27">Éter 12:27</a>; cursiva agregada).</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note16-"><span class="label">16. </span><p data-aid="138770943" id="note16_p1">Véanse <a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/nt/matt/14.html?verse=13-21#p13" href="/scriptures/nt/matt/14.13-21?lang=spa#p13">Mateo 14:13–21</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/nt/mark/6.html?verse=31-44#p31" href="/scriptures/nt/mark/6.31-44?lang=spa#p31">Marcos 6:31–44</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/nt/luke/9.html?verse=10-17#p10" href="/scriptures/nt/luke/9.10-17?lang=spa#p10">Lucas 9:10–17</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/nt/john/6.html?verse=1-14#p1" href="/scriptures/nt/john/6.1-14?lang=spa#p1">Juan 6:1–14</a>.</p></li><li class="footnote" id="note17-"><span class="label">17. </span><p data-aid="138770945" id="note17_p1"><a class="scripture-ref" data-old-href="../../../../scriptures/nt/john/6.html?verse=9#p9" href="/scriptures/nt/john/6.9?lang=spa#p9">Juan 6:9</